Description: Here is a very cool Jackson  JS Series "Custom Shack " Dinky Electric Guitar.  The maple/rosewood reverse headstock  neck is from  a Jackson JS Series and has  near zero fret wear . The very cool Satin Black body is from a JS 22,and all the hardware is black,I do not have the black push in whammy bar.. Body has  just light surface scratches. The pickups have been upgraded with some Hot HMV Black/White Zebra humbuckers,about 7.5k-neck,15k-bridge. I also installed a push/pull tone control so that you can split the humbuckers to single coils just by pulling up the tone knob. This gives you six different pickup combinations when used with the three way switch.  All electronics work perfectly,and sound great on every setting,clean or with some distortion. No joke these pickups sound killer on this guitar. The capacitor has been upgraded with a  Orange Drop style .022uf epoxy  capacitor,more range of tone control and a smoother response.  This "Custom Shack" came out great!!! One of the better guitars I have built in a while. A very sexy looking guitar,great colors. Action is  good and  could probably lowered even more. Guitar plays,looks,and sounds great. Please look carefully at all the pictures,they are part of the description too.This one  sounds very good. A very cool guitar period!
